# Build-context exclusions for `docker build` / `flyctl deploy`.
#
# The Dockerfile uses explicit COPY commands (package.json, server.mjs,
# and node_modules from the deps stage), so files NOT in those COPY
# commands cannot be included in the final image. But every file in
# the build directory is uploaded to the Docker daemon as the build
# context, which (a) slows the build proportional to the size of the
# directory, and (b) creates a defense-in-depth risk that a future
# Dockerfile change adding a wider COPY pattern could accidentally
# include credentials or local-only files. The .dockerignore closes
# both concerns.

# Local development node_modules (the image installs its own).
node_modules/

# Environment files (Fly.io secrets are the prod path; .env is local only).
.env
.env.*

# Service-account credentials (defense-in-depth alongside the project
# root .gitignore which already excludes these from version control).
*-firebase-adminsdk-*.json
service-account-*.json

# Local logs and debug output.
*.log
fly-debug.log

# Test and build artifacts.
*.tgz
dist/
coverage/

# Editor / OS files.
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# Git metadata (the image does not need .git).
.git/
.gitignore

# Docker config itself.
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
